article.headline: (22) SOUTH CAROLINA 99, WOFFORD 46
article.linkText: Gamecocks' Penn ties school record with 50 points in rout
article.story:
COLUMBIA, South Carolina (Ticker) -- Jocelyn Penn matched a 
school scoring record, but it may have came at the expense of
good sportsmanship.

Penn made 22-of-28 shots for a career-high 50 points as No. 22
South Carolina cruised to a 99-46 rout of Wofford.

South Carolina (5-0) was determined to give Penn a shot at
breaking Shannon Johnson's record. It pressed and fouled down
the stretch and allowed Penn to score the Lady Gamecocks' final
12 points in a game it led by 32 points at halftime.

Penn missed a layup with four seconds left that would have
broken the record. She scored 26 points on 12-of-14 shooting in
the first half and her 22 baskets set a school record.

Petra Ujheyli collected 16 points and 15 rebounds and Kelly
Morrone had 10 points and 11 assists for the Lady Gamecocks.

Wofford (1-4) shot just 31 percent (18-of-58) and committed 21
turnovers. Brie Bradshaw scored 14 points, but Ricaye Harris
missed all 11 shots.
